#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:3
#: 7e20df637fc34bda8c6306aeab9bdc8b
msgid "How to use optical discs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:6
#: f773ff9791dd4430afa10efc0924f867
msgid ""
"Passthrough reading and recording (a.k.a., “burning”) are not supported "
"by Qubes OS. This is not a limitation of Xen, which provides scsiback and"
" scsifront drivers, but of Qubes OS. It will be fixed in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:8
#: 68a4737ba42741bd993dd88652f0b767
msgid ""
"Currently, the only options for reading and recording optical discs "
"(e.g., CDs, DVDs, BRDs) in Qubes are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:10
#: f01960e040c746bf9e615fc795533d0e
msgid "Use a USB optical drive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:12
#: 27d4a15141ed4a47b76237cfdd087875
msgid ""
"Attach a SATA optical drive to a secondary SATA controller, then assign "
"this secondary SATA controller to a VM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:14
#: a8f74627f1454538acadd7a39077553b
msgid ""
"Use a SATA optical drive attached to dom0. (**Caution:** This option is "
"`potentially dangerous <https://forum.qubes-"
"os.org/t/19075#dom0-precautions>`__.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-optical-discs.rst:18
#: ccc6abc694a743899074631856d26ff7
msgid ""
"To access an optical disc via USB follow the :ref:`typical procedure for "
"attaching a USB device <user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-usb-devices:with "
"the command line tool>`, then check with the **Qubes Devices** widget to "
"see what device in the target qube the USB optical drive was attached to."
" Typically this would be ``sr0``. For example, if ``sys-usb`` has device "
"``3-2`` attached to the ``work`` qube’s ``sr0``, you would mount it with "
"``mount /dev/sr0 /mnt/removable``. You could also write to a disc with "
"``wodim -v dev=/dev/sr0 -eject /home/user/Qubes.iso``."
msgstr ""

